body:
Champion (Calem x reader)

A/n- You’re the current champion in the Kalos region until you are battled by Calem. It took him 6 attempts,but he finally beat you. You seem to have a very good ‘friendship’ after this.

Masterlist

—

“Back again?” You chuckles while you stood up from your seat. “It’s the sixth time.” “Sixth time lucky.” He said, blushing. He was quite shy. “I’ve been training a lot harder.” “Let’s see then.” You said, as you sent out your first Pokémon, Xerneas.

Your battle went on for a while, and it seemed to be going in your favour. That was until Calem and you were both on your last Pokémon. You were impressed with how much he had improved. You wouldn’t be surprised if he beat you this time. Finally, he hit your Pokémon with a move and it fainted.

You looked at eachother for a moment in total shock, before reacting. You both grinned at eachother brightly. “I’m impressed; That was amazing.” You said as you walked over and gave him a hug. At first he was stiff, but after a few seconds he hugged you back. You pulled away and laughed. “You’ll have to be battling me from now on.” He said as he smiled. He then suddenly looked worried. “You’re ok though, right?” “Of course, you deserve it.” You said as you gave him a reassuring smile.

You were a little bit sad about not being champion anymore, but it gave you the freedom to do more of the other things you have always wanted to do. You were also really happy for Calem.

You and Calem walked down the mountain together. “How do you feel? Being the new champion and all.” You asked him, glancing at him. “It hasn’t really hit me yet, but I know I’m really, really happy.” He beamed just thinking about it.

-

Once the new champion was announced to the people of Kalos, big celebrations were held across the region. You attended the one that was held by the elite four and the champion himself.

You had just excused yourself from the party and you were now standing on the balcony of the hotel. You stared in awe at how beautiful Lumios city was. The bright lights lit up the city like a Christmas tree. You began thinking about what you were going to do now, when Calem walked out onto the balcony and over to you.

You greeted eachother and began chatting about random things before you started to get more deep. “What are you going to do now?” He said, but you gave him a confused look, so he continued. “You know, now that your not the champion.” “Ohhhh…yeah. I think I’m going to go and explore Kalos again. I haven’t explored since I started my Pokémon journey.” You explained as you stared into the distance. You looked over at Calem, who was frowning. “I’ll be able to see you though, right?” He questioned. “Definitely. I can come and visit all the time, I don’t think I could last very long without seeing you.” You laughed and blushed pink. “I’m glad.” Calem said smiling. You suddenly had a lot of confidence. “Would you wanna go out on, like, a date sometime?” You asked and looked over at him. His eyes shone and he blushed. “Yeah, that would be good. I would like that a lot.”

You both chatted for a bit longer, before going back inside and joining in with the party.

blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Deerling and Sawsbuck
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Deerling and Sawsbuck
body:
585: Deerling

Oh yeah, also an often-forgotten fact by now, Gen 5 introduced a seasons system that was swiftly ditched once we moved on to the next Gen. Which makes things awkward for our friend of the day here, Deerling.

As per Gamefreak tradition, whenever they release some major new feature, they have to also introduce a new Pokemon whose primary function is to make use of said feature. As I’ve so very very subtly implied, Deerling here changes its appearance based on the season, somewhat. Main thing being its coat changes color based on the season. Up above is Spring; oft treated as Deerling’s default, and down below are the Summer, Autumn, and Winter forms respectively.

And what a cute deer friend we have here!! Before Gen 5 here, a deer (that isn’t Stantler) has been on my Pokemon wishlist for some time, and Deerling doesn’t disappoint! I personally may have done a deer Pokemon with a different approach, but I still love Deerling for being a cute idea with fun execution. It’s just a shame that in Gen 6 and 7, Deerling is missing out on its main gimmick. And I’m not even sure if the non-spring forms are even available in the games right now. Whether that be you can somehow “trick” Deerling into thinking it’s a different season or if a Deerling transferred from Gen 5 will keep its seasonal form.

Personal Score: 10/10

Absolutely perfectly adorable deer child

586: Sawsbuck

While they’re still only aesthetic differences, its seasonal variation is a lot more apparent in Sawsbuck. Who, in a perfect meshing of plant and animal, has tree branches for antlers. If you ask me, the Spring form is the weakest one just because that fact is rather downplayed when it didn’t have to be. It might’ve been best if they just went for a full-blown cherry blossom look. …I mean, that is what they were going for, from what I can tell, but y'know.

The Summer variant also looks a bit more like a default form than the Spring form does. Predictably, this is the most leafy form where the tree-antlers are the most like a tree. And… apparently summer calls for giving this deer a freaking suffer-dude mullet. Now I can’t unsee it. Dammit.

Now anyone that knows their trivia about Matt will know that Autumn is, especially aesthetically, my favorite season of the year! And Sawsbuck’s Autumn form doesn’t disappoint at all. And is in fact, my favorite form of this ‘mon! That’s just such a good, Autumn-leafy red right there.

Actually, this might be more like a default form than even the Summer form. With this look here, you’d might just assume it was just a winter-themed deer Pokemon. Though I might call it second-favorite, just because I like wintery-looking reindeerish things.

Personal Score: 9/10

Maybe not my quintessential deer Pokemon, but it’s dang close if ya ask me.

Overall:

Finally. A nice deer Pokemon.

[Archive]

I personally may have done a deer Pokemon with a different approach, but I still love Deerling for being a cute idea with fun execution. It’s just a shame that in Gen 6 and 7, Deerling is missing out on its main gimmick. And I’m not even sure if the non-spring forms are even available in the games right now. Whether that be you can somehow “trick” Deerling into thinking it’s a different season or if a Deerling transferred from Gen 5 will keep its seasonal form.

Personal Score: 10/10

Absolutely perfectly adorable deer child

586: Sawsbuck

While they’re still only aesthetic differences, its seasonal variation is a lot more apparent in Sawsbuck. Who, in a perfect meshing of plant and animal, has tree branches for antlers. If you ask me, the Spring form is the weakest one just because that fact is rather downplayed when it didn’t have to be. It might’ve been best if they just went for a full-blown cherry blossom look. …I mean, that is what they were going for, from what I can tell, but y'know.

The Summer variant also looks a bit more like a default form than the Spring form does. Predictably, this is the most leafy form where the tree-antlers are the most like a tree. And… apparently summer calls for giving this deer a freaking suffer-dude mullet. Now I can’t unsee it. Dammit.

Now anyone that knows their trivia about Matt will know that Autumn is, especially aesthetically, my favorite season of the year! And Sawsbuck’s Autumn form doesn’t disappoint at all. And is in fact, my favorite form of this ‘mon! That’s just such a good, Autumn-leafy red right there.

Actually, this might be more like a default form than even the Summer form. With this look here, you’d might just assume it was just a winter-themed deer Pokemon. Though I might call it second-favorite, just because I like wintery-looking reindeerish things.

Personal Score: 9/10

Maybe not my quintessential deer Pokemon, but it’s dang close if ya ask me.

Overall:

Finally. A nice deer Pokemon.
